At Gusii Stadium former giants Shabana FC outwitted bottom place Murang'a Seal 3-1 to move to fifth position on the table on 15 points.Murang'a Seal, who are yet to win any match this season, took the lead in early stages of the game, but Kevin Nyabuto levelled for Shabana before half time. Bryan Messi added the second, while Enock Momanyi stretched Shabana's lead late in the game.  Police FC bagged maximum points to stay at the summit of National Super League without kicking a ball after Mount Kenya issued a walkover in their league match on Sunday.
The match was supposed to be played at Camp Toyoyo, but ironically Mount Kenya (formerly Nakumatt) failed to show up due to financial constraints.



